<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="811" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d811">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/257: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-20T19:00:00-04:00">April 20,
                                    1942—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>157. Further to our cable 145 of April 10 [<hi rend="italic">14</hi>]
                            with particular reference to suggestion of enlarging existing Ankara
                            Co-ordinating Committee by United States representation, Department
                            feels advisable that two such representatives be provisionally
                            designated at this time.</p>
                        <pb facs="0707" n="695" xml:id="pg_695"/>
                        <p>You and the military attaché are so designated. War Department has given
                            the necessary approval for the latter. Any additional personnel will be
                            left to your discretion, as is also the authority to designate a member
                            of your staff to attend meetings on your behalf when desirable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>